{
  "stem": "11593.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And especially when they occupied Austria and Czechoslovakia, I could detect a nervousness in the community.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "More people were reading more newspapers, listening to the radio.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We have picked up refugees that left Austria, Vienna, and Prague.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My dad and some of his friends, since we had a big house, the affluent Jewish community would go to the station and pick up those refugees and bring them to our home to stay with us.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The refugees, majority were physicians and engineers that escaped-- were able to escape.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And that life went on till 1939.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "In September 1939, Germany attacked Poland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We see a bunch of more relatives.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "A lot were-- my mother's couple of-- two ladies, very good friends, came in.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they said their sons were killed in the fighting in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They were officers in the Polish army.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "This exchange became very sad.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They bombed our city, and fortunately, all the bombs fell in the fields.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Our town was a small town but a beautiful town.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The streets were cobblestones.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "The sidewalks were nice flowers, cement sidewalks.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "The-- the houses were mostly single- and two-family houses.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It was a peaceful town.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Next town to us was city of Rovno, with it 50,000 to 60,000 inhabitants, of which 2/3 were Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Over there, they had gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They had more institutions of learning.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "They had a yeshiva.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And they had a lot of teams, you know, soccer teams and boxing teams.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "We-- in those days, we also had a Zionist movement, where people on the-- from Ze'ev Jabotinsky's the Betar group-- used to come to our town, encourage the Jewish people to immigrate to Israel and leave.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Well, it seems like [POLISH] was a little too late, and the people were in a dilemma.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
